The DA says it wants Mkhwebane to look into the highly irregular payout to establish on what basis Molefe received the amount. JOHANNESBURG The Democratic Alliance (DA) says it will be writing to Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane to request that she investigate an alleged R30 million pension pay out to former Eskom CEO Brian Molefe.According to theSunday Times, the golden handshake was paid out to Molefe by the power utility in March, after just 18 months in the position.He resigned from Eskom last year after details of his relationship with the Gupta family were revealed in former Public Protector Thuli Madonsela's State of Capture report.The DA says it wants Mkhwebane to look into the highly irregular payout to establish on what basis Molefe received the amount.Shadow minister for public enterprises Natasha Mazzone said, This points to gross funds abuse, it s outrageous that after only 18 months of being CEO of the power utility Molefe is awarded such a massive bonus. 